offer techniques for writing and publicising your research. The Routledge Companion to Design Research will have wide appeal to researchers and educators in design and design-related disciplines such as engineering, business, marketing, computing, and will make an invaluable contribution to state-of-the-art design research at postgraduate, doctoral, and post-doctoral levels and teaching across a wide range of different disciplines"--cProvided by publisher.  aDescription based on print version record.  a44 0aDesignxResearch.1 aRodgers, Paul A.,eeditor.1 aYee, Joyce,eeditor.403University of Alberta Accessuhttp://search.ebscohost.com/login.aspx?direct=true&scope=site&db=nlebk&db=nlabk&AN=873099z(Single User Access)  aInternet AccesshUAINzPDAOWNED  aInternet AccesswLCc1i6773216-1001lINTERNETmUAINTERNETrYsYtE-RESOURCEu1/12/2015xE-BOOKzPDAOWNED01ahttp://id.loc.gov/authorities/names/no2013128044bhttp://viaf.org/viaf/305353353